{
  "stem": "10353.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we didn't realize that the guards from the tower with their search lights-- they were going on constantly-- that they saw us doing that.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when they were relieved at midnight, they-- he came down and he started to yell and he cocked up his rifle.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he says, you guys were stealing, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We saw you from the-- What were we stealing?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Nothing.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he cocked up his rifle.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was the lucky one that he picked out, ready to shoot.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he didn't shoot, because this huge kapo, this Greek kapo came and he started to slap me around and he knocked me to the ground.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that sort of calmed down the German.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and he let me go.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And anyway, we pumped that water 'til 6 o'clock in the morning, at which time we were relieved and hauled back into the barrack.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the following afternoon we were hauled out again to another cistern to do the same thing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And at that time-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] at that time, I-- we were again next to a kitchen where were heaps of turnips were there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And people became [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In this they-- they tied up their pants, and they were dropping the turnips into their pants.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[SIGHS] I was a little bit smarter at that time and I didn't do it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And lo and behold again, the-- and from the tower, the guard saw that.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And when he was relieved, he came down and he started to make a ruckus that we were stealing turnips.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "By-- by that time-- put a pillow over it-- by that time, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the officers, the oberscharfuhrer and all the SS came and they started to haul in the-- round up the guys.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they got a terrific beating, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The kapos came, the Ukrainians, and they pulled them over a barrel, you know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they were with huge, huge sticks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they were beating them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, two dies-- two guys died there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They knocked off their-- their kidneys.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] This was towards the end of March.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And April came in and the-- the-- the weather got a little bit milder.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we were given the-- the task to clean out all the trenches and the-- and-- and the gutters, you know, that were also filled with all kinds of debris.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And at that time we came closer to a camp-- to a stalag that contained some of the boys with the striped pajamas.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "That was immediately after the Dutch stalag.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And lo and behold, as I was cleaning the gutter, we were talking to them through the fence.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And quite a number of my schoolmates that I was going to school with them from back home, from my hometown, they were in that stalag.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I didn't-- they were beyond recognition.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "They were already so emaciated that they would be-- I just couldn't recognize them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "In any event, to this went on 'til around April the 7th or the 8th, when all of a sudden we got word that our stalag will be evacuated.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And we were divided in two groups.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "One group was to leave one day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And the next group was to leave the other day, the following day.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And we were marched out from the camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And we didn't know where we are going, but we were told that we are going.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "That's all.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we were again put into freight cars.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And little did we know by that time that the British army was only about 8 to 10 kilometers away from us.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And we were taken out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We were evacuated.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "But the way we went to the train-- to the railway station, there were columns of hundreds and hundreds of hundreds emaciated people coming, you know, that could hardly walk, that they were dragging themselves, urged on by the SS with-- with all kinds of beatings.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And we were going on one side of the road.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "They were on the other side of the road.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "In any event, we were put into the wagons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And we were taken-- the-- the train pulled out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And we were traveling we didn't know where.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "We didn't know nothing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "By that time, the SS that were escorting us were a little bit on the milder side.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "They were-- they were in a separate wagon, and they let us get out of our wagons to go out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "And as a matter of fact, we came in to a city called Luneburg, something, Luneburg.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And it was immediately after that particular railway station was heavily bombarded by the Allies.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And the freight cars were filled with food, with cigarettes, with chocolates, with everything.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
